{% comment %}
  snippets/collection-promo.liquid
  [1.2.1 → 1] Placement layer — decides which blocks fire at a given row.

  Called by collection-products.liquid after each product row closes.
  Iterates section.blocks, finds any whose `row` setting matches the
  current row_index, and delegates each to promo-block.liquid.

  Parameters:
    blocks     {Array}   required — section.blocks forwarded from collection.liquid
    row_index  {Number}  required — 1-based row number just completed

  Owns:
    - Row-matching logic only
    - Nothing else — no markup of its own

  Does NOT own:
    - Block markup (promo-block.liquid)
    - Block-type routing (promo-block.liquid)
    - Individual block rendering (banner-image / product-carousel / collection-carousel)

  Pitfall — multiple blocks at the same row:
    Multiple blocks can share the same `row` value. This is intentional:
    e.g. a 50% banner + a 50% banner side-by-side in one row slot.
    collection-promo renders all matching blocks; promo-block handles
    width so they sit correctly in a flex row.
{% endcomment %}

{%- for block in blocks -%}
  {%- if block.settings.row == row_index -%}
    {%- render 'promo-block', block: block -%}
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endfor -%}
